      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:05:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Should we leave exception_code in the client’s control, or just send our magic one via this interface?",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "88656498_a9dd0b5a",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client.h",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 169,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:46:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think if the client is controlling the thread id, it seems reasonable that they might want to set a particular exception code that makes sense to them. But it probably doesn\u0027t matter too much. I can remove it if you think it\u0027s more clear.",
      "parentUuid": "089a54ee_df541fd3",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_ff6b9b7b",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client.h",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 169,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T20:20:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You can leave it if you want, it was just something that struck me as maybe more control than the client needs.",
      "parentUuid": "88656498_a9dd0b5a",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
