    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_1f4f673d",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 508,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:05:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I match “* 1024” better than “\u003c\u003c 10”.\n\nI trust that our tests will catch any case in which 4kB isn’t enough. I don’t anticipate it being too little, we just need enough to raise the exception and run the unhandled exception filter, which we’ve intentionally kept very simple.",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "88656498_a978abfd",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 508,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:46:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We need \u003c 100 bytes at the moment, but it\u0027s going to be a full page in any case.\n\nI guess we could get unlucky after a complicated refactor and end up allocating this right next to other memory that was writable, and then overflow into it. Added a DCHECK that we don\u0027t exceed the limit before the WriteProcessMemory().",
      "parentUuid": "089a54ee_1f4f673d",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_3f4c2346",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 510,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:05:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Beneficial to make this read-write while we’re splatting stuff into it and then read-execute when we’re ready to inject the thread?",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "88656498_298cbb61",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 510,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:46:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t see any upside to doing that. The fewer calls we make here, the better, I think.",
      "parentUuid": "089a54ee_3f4c2346",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_1f812779",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 510,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T20:20:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The security guys always seem to want W xor X, but maybe not on Windows? I thought that it was because having a page that was both at the same time made it easier to abuse, but if it’s xor, your attack’s got to have spot-on timing or else it’ll just crash.",
      "parentUuid": "88656498_298cbb61",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_7f46ab27",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 519,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:05:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I doubt you need to do this. Can’t you just say \u0026RaiseException?",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "88656498_499c8f93",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 519,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:46:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hah, GetProcAddress() on the brain. Done.",
      "parentUuid": "089a54ee_7f46ab27",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_bf8833a8",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 589,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:05:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Where’s the stack for this new thread? The same question applies for x86_64. Even though the code you wrote there doesn’t use the stack, RaiseException() might, and the unhandled exception filter definitely will.",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "88656498_f4b756f6",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 589,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:46:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, the injected stack will get the default stack size from the target\u0027s PE header: https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms686774(v\u003dvs.85).aspx . Are you thinking maybe we want to try to squish it smaller?",
      "parentUuid": "089a54ee_bf8833a8",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_7f786b4b",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 589,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T20:20:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I just wasn’t clear on whether NtCreateThreadEx() used the default or if that was a higher-level CreateThread()/CreateRemoteThread() thing.\n\nIf there’s no chance of running anyone else’s code on our new thread’s stack, I’d say we should make it smaller to reduce the risk of running out of address space. But if there’s an avenue to run something else (via VEH?) then we should probably leave it at the default.",
      "parentUuid": "88656498_f4b756f6",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_9f83778d",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 594,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:05:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can you stick some poison here like hlt in case of an unexpected return from RaiseException()?",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "88656498_b4ca3e6a",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 594,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:46:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How about ud2, since hlt is ring 0? Done. (Not in the x64 case, since there\u0027s no way we can return there.)",
      "parentUuid": "089a54ee_9f83778d",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_bfdaf393",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 594,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T20:20:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right, hlt raises #gp. #gp vs. #ud, doesn’t make much of a difference to me. ud2’s good, I just didn’t want an errant return (from a debugger?) to try executing garbage and make things worse.",
      "parentUuid": "88656498_b4ca3e6a",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_dfdfbf82",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 594,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T20:20:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh, and in the x86_64 case, RaiseException can still try to return, but it’ll jump to (a garbage address? the thing that our entry point would have returned to?) I don’t know if NtCreateThreadEx() sets things up so that the entry point can return or whether it cares about the return value.",
      "parentUuid": "88656498_b4ca3e6a",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_ff92bbd3",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 639,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:05:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Surprised to see this, since it’s not required on x86 and that’s all that we support.",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "88656498_74dda625",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 639,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T19:46:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, true. It is documented as being required per Remarks in https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms679350(v\u003dvs.85).aspx and Raymond even says it might be https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/oldnewthing/20031208-00/?p\u003d41583 (though I think he may be mistaken). But yeah, it doesn\u0027t actually do anything. I can remove it if you prefer.",
      "parentUuid": "089a54ee_ff92bbd3",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "089a54ee_ffe47b57",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 639,
      "author": {
        "id": 1143760
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-21T20:20:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We can leave it as you have it to humor Raymond, but he’s way off base.",
      "parentUuid": "88656498_74dda625",
      "revId": "0f544b3e831c2d4d922a8fc70f6d60534ed83288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
